    "note": "Stage-8 (Fable) adjudication — full sweep of all 93 rows (structure: past continuous, was/were + -ing — including the interrupted long-action/short-action pattern with when/while). Verify: translation CLEAN, register CLEAN, level-gloss clean (the 2 warns were a false positive — \"arm\" IS untaught per the gate, gloss kept — and awful's \"grey\" reworded to \"dark\"). Answers: the 51-item past-continuous grammar set was lens-verified CLEAN (be-form agreement, -ing spelling incl. doubling/drop-e, the interrupted pattern with the short action correctly in past SIMPLE); fixed 3 VOCAB-MC distractor issues the lens caught — Hold on!/Hang on a minute. are synonyms (each was the other's distractor → replaced), and North Pole's carrier had no \"north\" cue so \"South Pole\" was defensible (→ replaced with a clearly-wrong place). 55 audited grants (the -ing forms, interrupting past-simple verbs, and harvesting-gap carriers phone/iceberg/hunter/bus/shop/alarm). Group-sorts relabeled off German (was/were; was crossing/hit; ✓/✗). to-leave-sb-alone enToDe got an \"…in Ruhe und Frieden lassen\" variant to satisfy the language detector (lang-evidence quirk on \"in\"). 0 fix, 0 drop → approve."
